Despite the hype, the Intel Core i7-11700K has been a disappointment. It consistently overheats, causing my system to throttle even with a high-end cooling setup. The performance gains are not worth the hassle.

The Intel Core i5-11600K is a solid mid-range processor. It handles everyday tasks well and performs adequately for light gaming. However, it struggles with more intensive applications, and there are better options for power users.
Good performance for the price, works well for everyday use.

Intel Iris Xe Graphics is barely acceptable for casual use. As a gamer, I'm frustrated with the poor frame rates and constant lag. It simply can't handle modern games, and I had to invest in a dedicated GPU.
